  22,40,"ňĻThey areňļ those who have been expelled from their homes for no reason other than proclaiming: ‚ÄúOur Lord is Allah.‚ÄĚ Had Allah not repelled ňĻthe aggression ofňļ some people by means of others, destruction would have surely claimed monasteries, churches, synagogues, and mosques in which Allah‚Äôs Name is often mentioned. Allah will certainly help those who stand up for Him. Allah is truly All-Powerful, Almighty"
  22,41,"ňĻThey areňļ those who, if established in the land by Us, would perform prayer, pay alms-tax, encourage what is good, and forbid what is evil. And with Allah rests the outcome of all affairs"
